$selectMenu:
creates a select menu with options;Example: $selectMenu[
        {id=Menu id}
        {placeholder=Place holder}
        {min=Minimum allowed selected options}
        {max=Maximum allowed selected options}
        {disabled=If menu is disabled or not (yes/no)}
        {label=Option 1 name}
        {desc=Option 1 description}
        {value=Option 1 value}
        {emoji=Option 1 emoji}

        {label=Option 2 name}
        {desc=Option 2 description}
        {value=Option 2 value}
        {emoji=Option 2 emoji}
        ...

    ]
Example2:
$selectMenu[
{id=id}
{placeholder=Please select your anwser!}
{min=1}
{max=2}
{label=Option one }
{desc=txt for one}
{value=one}
{emoji=$customEmoji[accept]}
{label=Option two }
{desc=txt for two}
{value=two}
{emoji=$customEmoji[reject]}
]
Supports upto 20 options

$arrayMap:
To replace array values to another value
**Note:** Only zero-cooldown functions allowed in CODE;$arrayMap[Element Value;Element Index;array name (optional)]{
CODE...
}

Example:
$textSplit[15,18,21;,]
$arrayMap[age]{
age is $age
}
$arrayJoin[, ]

Output:
age is 15, age is 18, age is 21

$arrayFilter:
To filter an array depend on a value of CODE, if `false` then remove that element from the array
**Note:** Only zero-cooldown functions allowed in CODE;$arrayFilter[Element Value;Element Index;array name]{
CODE...
}

Example (Remove Hello):
$textSplit[Hello/World;/]
$arrayFilter[value]{
$if[$value==Hello]{
false
}
}
$arrayJoin[/]

Output:
World

$awaitMenu:
To wait for a menu option to be selected and return the selected options values
In case of no option selected, it return **undefined**
In case of multiple values selected, all of them will return with `,` as seperator;$awaitMenu[Message (optional);user id (optional, default:author);timeout (optional, default:15s);menu id1 (optional);menu id2...]

Example:

You selected: $awaitMenu[
{title: Test}
{menu:
    {id=test}
    {placeholder=Select}
    {min=1}
    {max=1}
    {label=Mido}
    {desc=A guy}
    {value=mido}
    {label=Rake}
    {desc=Another guy}
    {value=rake}
}
;$authorID;;test]

Output:

You selected: rake

$editEmbed:
edit embed in given message;$editEmbed[channel id (optional);message id (optional);New data (curl);Embed Number (optional, default 1)]

Example:
$editEmbed[$channelID;$messageID;
{title:New title}
]

$buffer:
It return the input (useful for some rare cases);$buffer[input]

Example:
$sendMessage[{footer:$buffer[Some :Breaking  :Message]}

$modal:
Send a modal, it will only work in interaction-related triggers
**Note**: You can only use this within 2 seconds of execution;$modal[
{title=Modal Title}
{id=Modal ID (anything)}
{input=
	{name=Input name}
	{ph=Input Placeholder}
	{id=Input ID}
	{type=short/long}
	{min=Minimum length}
	{max=Maximum Length}
	{required=yes/no}
	{def=Default value}
}]

$arrayLoop:
To loop over the array
**Note:** Only zero-cooldown functions allowed in CODE;$arrayLoop[varname;index;array name (optional)]{
CODE...
}

Example:
$textSplit[15,18,21;,]
$arrayLoop[age]{
age is $age
}

Output:
age is 15
age is 18
age is 21

$ObjectLoop:
To loop over the object
**Note:** Only zero-cooldown functions allowed in CODE;$ObjectLoop[key name;value name;index name;Nested Prroperty 1;Nested Property 2;...]{
CODE...
}

Example:
$objectSet[Mido;Sword]
$objectSet[Rake;Staff]
$objectLoop[name;weapon;index]{
$index. $name has $weapon
}

Output:
1. Mido has Sword
2. Rake has Staff

$addMenu:
Add a menu to existing message;$addMenu[
        {channel=channel id}
        {message=message id}
        {id=Menu ID}
        {ph=Placeholder}

        {label=Option 1 Label}
        {desc=Option 1 Description}
        {value=Option 1 ID}
        {emoji=Option 1 Emoji}

        {label=Option 2 Label}
        {desc=Option 2 Description}
        {value=Option 2 ID}
        {emoji=Option 2 Emoji}
        ...
    ]

Example:
$addMenu[
        {chid=$channelID}
        {mid=1151607052007907449}
        {id=mymenu}
        {label=Rake}
        {value=rake}

        {label=Mido}
        {value=mido}]
